<TITLE> Col Ashraf appointed IG prisons </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jul 26 (bdnews24.com)The government has appointed additional inspector general of prisons Col Ashraful Islam Khan as acting inspector general of prisons, removing Brig Gen AHM Mokbul Hossain, an establishment ministry order said Sunday. Ashraful has been appointed on deputation, while Mokbul who was also on deputation has been moved to the Armed Forces Division. Lt Col Syed Iftekhar Uddin has between made a new additional inspector general of prisons. The government has also made some other changes in the positions of deputed armed forces officers. Col Shamsul Huq has been appointed director of the National Security Intelligence. The government has moved defence ministry joint secretary Brig Gen Mohammad Zahidur Rahman to the Armed Forces Division prior to his return to the army, while Col Taufiqul Anam has taken up the joint secretary chair. Col Mohammad Abdul Mazid Bhuiyan has been appointed director, adminisitration, of Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Medical University. Col ABM Sayeful Islam has been made deputy director general of Ansar and VDP forces. Deputy managing director of Sena Kalyan Sangstha (Army Welfare Organisation), Lt Col Ali Ahmed Khan, has been moved to the Armed Forces Division prior to returning to his earlier army post. bdn
